field_details.description: Output only. The number of campaigns attached to this bidding strategy. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.campaign_count

field_details.description: Immutable. The currency used by the bidding strategy (ISO 4217 three-letter code). For bidding strategies in manager customers, this currency can be set on creation and defaults to the manager customer's currency. For serving customers, this field cannot be set; all strategies in a serving customer implicitly use the serving customer's currency. In all cases the effective_currency_code field returns the currency used by the strategy.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.currency_code

field_details.description: Output only. The currency used by the bidding strategy (ISO 4217 three-letter code). For bidding strategies in manager customers, this is the currency set by the advertiser when creating the strategy. For serving customers, this is the customer's currency_code. Bidding strategy metrics are reported in this currency. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.effective_currency_code

field_details.description: A bidding strategy that raises bids for clicks that seem more likely to lead to a conversion and lowers them for clicks where they seem less likely.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.enhanced_cpc

field_details.description: Output only. The ID of the bidding strategy.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.id

field_details.description: Output only. The target return on ad spend (ROAS) option. If set, the bid strategy will maximize revenue while averaging the target return on ad spend. If the target ROAS is high, the bid strategy may not be able to spend the full budget. If the target ROAS is not set, the bid strategy will aim to achieve the highest possible ROAS for the budget.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.maximize_conversion_value.target_roas

field_details.description: The target cost-per-action (CPA) option. This is the average amount that you would like to spend per conversion action. If set, the bid strategy will get as many conversions as possible at or below the target cost-per-action. If the target CPA is not set, the bid strategy will aim to achieve the lowest possible CPA given the budget.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.maximize_conversions.target_cpa

field_details.description: The name of the bidding strategy. All bidding strategies within an account must be named distinctly. The length of this string should be between 1 and 255, inclusive, in UTF-8 bytes, (trimmed).
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.name

field_details.description: Output only. The number of non-removed campaigns attached to this bidding strategy. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.non_removed_campaign_count

field_details.description: Immutable. The resource name of the bidding strategy. Bidding strategy resource names have the form: `customers/{customer_id}/biddingStrategies/{bidding_strategy_id}`
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.resource_name

field_details.description: Output only. The status of the bidding strategy. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.status

field_details.description: Maximum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy. This should only be set for portfolio bid strategies.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_cpa.cpc_bid_ceiling_micros

field_details.description: Minimum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy. This should only be set for portfolio bid strategies.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_cpa.cpc_bid_floor_micros

field_details.description: Average CPA target. This target should be greater than or equal to minimum billable unit based on the currency for the account.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_cpa.target_cpa_micros

field_details.description: Output only. The highest CPC bid the automated bidding system is permitted to specify. This is a required field entered by the advertiser that sets the ceiling and specified in local micros.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_impression_share.cpc_bid_ceiling_micros

field_details.description: Output only. The targeted location on the search results page.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_impression_share.location

field_details.description: The desired fraction of ads to be shown in the targeted location in micros. E.g. 1% equals 10,000.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_impression_share.location_fraction_micros

field_details.description: Maximum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy. This should only be set for portfolio bid strategies.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_roas.cpc_bid_ceiling_micros

field_details.description: Minimum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy. This should only be set for portfolio bid strategies.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_roas.cpc_bid_floor_micros

field_details.description: Output only. The desired revenue (based on conversion data) per unit of spend.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_roas.target_roas

field_details.description: Output only. Maximum bid limit that can be set by the bid strategy. The limit applies to all keywords managed by the strategy.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_spend.cpc_bid_ceiling_micros

field_details.description: Output only. The spend target under which to maximize clicks. A TargetSpend bidder will attempt to spend the smaller of this value or the natural throttling spend amount. If not specified, the budget is used as the spend target. This field is deprecated and should no longer be used. See https://ads-developers.googleblog.com/2020/05/reminder-about-sunset-creation-of.html for details.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.target_spend.target_spend_micros

field_details.description: Output only. The type of the bidding strategy. Create a bidding strategy by setting the bidding scheme. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: bidding_strategy.type

field_details.description: Whether auto-tagging is enabled for the customer.
field_details.name: customer.auto_tagging_enabled

field_details.description: Customer-level call conversion action to attribute a call conversion to. If not set a default conversion action is used. Only in effect when call_conversion_reporting_enabled is set to true.
field_details.name: customer.call_reporting_setting.call_conversion_action

field_details.description: Whether to enable call conversion reporting.
field_details.name: customer.call_reporting_setting.call_conversion_reporting_enabled

field_details.description: Enable reporting of phone call events by redirecting them via Google System.
field_details.name: customer.call_reporting_setting.call_reporting_enabled

field_details.description: Output only. The conversion tracking id used for this account. This id is automatically assigned after any conversion tracking feature is used. If the customer doesn't use conversion tracking, this is 0. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: customer.conversion_tracking_setting.conversion_tracking_id

field_details.description: Output only. The conversion tracking id of the customer's manager. This is set when the customer is opted into cross account conversion tracking, and it overrides conversion_tracking_id. This field can only be managed through the Google Ads UI. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: customer.conversion_tracking_setting.cross_account_conversion_tracking_id

field_details.description: Immutable. The currency in which the account operates. A subset of the currency codes from the ISO 4217 standard is supported.
field_details.name: customer.currency_code

field_details.description: Optional, non-unique descriptive name of the customer.
field_details.name: customer.descriptive_name

field_details.description: The URL template for appending params to the final URL
field_details.name: customer.final_url_suffix

field_details.description: Output only. Whether the Customer has a Partners program badge. If the Customer is not associated with the Partners program, this will be false. For more information, see https://support.google.com/partners/answer/3125774.
field_details.name: customer.has_partners_badge

field_details.description: Output only. The ID of the customer.
field_details.name: customer.id

field_details.description: Output only. Whether the customer is a manager.
field_details.name: customer.manager

field_details.description: Output only. Optimization score of the customer. Optimization score is an estimate of how well a customer's campaigns are set to perform. It ranges from 0% (0.0) to 100% (1.0). This field is null for all manager customers, and for unscored non-manager customers. See "About optimization score" at https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/9061546. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: customer.optimization_score

field_details.description: Output only. Optimization score weight of the customer. Optimization score weight can be used to compare/aggregate optimization scores across multiple non-manager customers. The aggregate optimization score of a manager is computed as the sum over all of their customers of `Customer.optimization_score * Customer.optimization_score_weight`. This field is 0 for all manager customers, and for unscored non-manager customers. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: customer.optimization_score_weight

field_details.description: Output only. Reasons why the customer is not eligible to use PaymentMode.CONVERSIONS. If the list is empty, the customer is eligible. This field is read-only.
field_details.name: customer.pay_per_conversion_eligibility_failure_reasons

field_details.description: Output only. The Google global site tag.
field_details.name: customer.remarketing_setting.google_global_site_tag

field_details.description: Immutable. The resource name of the customer. Customer resource names have the form: `customers/{customer_id}`
field_details.name: customer.resource_name

field_details.description: Output only. Whether the customer is a test account.
field_details.name: customer.test_account

field_details.description: Immutable. The local timezone ID of the customer.
field_details.name: customer.time_zone

field_details.description: The URL template for constructing a tracking URL out of parameters.
field_details.name: customer.tracking_url_template

field_details.description: The total number of conversions. This includes all conversions regardless of the value of include_in_conversions_metric.
field_details.name: metrics.all_conversions

field_details.description: All conversions from interactions (as oppose to view through conversions) divided by the number of ad interactions.
field_details.name: metrics.all_conversions_from_interactions_rate

field_details.description: The value of all conversions.
field_details.name: metrics.all_conversions_value

field_details.description: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.
field_details.name: metrics.average_cpc

field_details.description: Average cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM).
field_details.name: metrics.average_cpm

field_details.description: The number of clicks.
field_details.name: metrics.clicks

field_details.description: The number of conversions. This only includes conversion actions which include_in_conversions_metric attribute is set to true. If you use conversion-based bidding, your bid strategies will optimize for these conversions.
field_details.name: metrics.conversions

field_details.description: Conversions from interactions divided by the number of ad interactions (such as clicks for text ads or views for video ads). This only includes conversion actions which include_in_conversions_metric attribute is set to true. If you use conversion-based bidding, your bid strategies will optimize for these conversions.
field_details.name: metrics.conversions_from_interactions_rate

field_details.description: The value of conversions. This only includes conversion actions which include_in_conversions_metric attribute is set to true. If you use conversion-based bidding, your bid strategies will optimize for these conversions.
field_details.name: metrics.conversions_value

field_details.description: The sum of your cost-per-click (CPC) and cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) costs during this period.
field_details.name: metrics.cost_micros

field_details.description: The cost of ad interactions divided by all conversions.
field_details.name: metrics.cost_per_all_conversions

field_details.description: The cost of ad interactions divided by conversions. This only includes conversion actions which include_in_conversions_metric attribute is set to true. If you use conversion-based bidding, your bid strategies will optimize for these conversions.
field_details.name: metrics.cost_per_conversion

field_details.description: Conversions from when a customer clicks on a Google Ads ad on one device, then converts on a different device or browser. Cross-device conversions are already included in all_conversions.
field_details.name: metrics.cross_device_conversions

field_details.description: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions).
field_details.name: metrics.ctr

field_details.description: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.
field_details.name: metrics.impressions

field_details.description: The value of all conversions divided by the number of all conversions.
field_details.name: metrics.value_per_all_conversions

field_details.description: The value of conversions divided by the number of conversions. This only includes conversion actions which include_in_conversions_metric attribute is set to true. If you use conversion-based bidding, your bid strategies will optimize for these conversions.
field_details.name: metrics.value_per_conversion

field_details.description: The total number of view-through conversions. These happen when a customer sees an image or rich media ad, then later completes a conversion on your site without interacting with (e.g., clicking on) another ad.
field_details.name: metrics.view_through_conversions

field_details.description: Resource name of the conversion action.
field_details.name: segments.conversion_action

field_details.description: Conversion action category.
field_details.name: segments.conversion_action_category

field_details.description: Conversion action name.
field_details.name: segments.conversion_action_name

field_details.description: Date to which metrics apply. yyyy-MM-dd format, e.g., 2018-04-17.
field_details.name: segments.date

field_details.description: Day of the week, e.g., MONDAY.
field_details.name: segments.day_of_week

field_details.description: Device to which metrics apply.
field_details.name: segments.device

field_details.description: External conversion source.
field_details.name: segments.external_conversion_source

field_details.description: Hour of day as a number between 0 and 23, inclusive.
field_details.name: segments.hour

field_details.description: Month as represented by the date of the first day of a month. Formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.
field_details.name: segments.month

field_details.description: Month of the year, e.g., January.
field_details.name: segments.month_of_year

field_details.description: Quarter as represented by the date of the first day of a quarter. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2018 starts on 2018-04-01. Formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.
field_details.name: segments.quarter

field_details.description: Week as defined as Monday through Sunday, and represented by the date of Monday. Formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.
field_details.name: segments.week

field_details.description: Year, formatted as yyyy.
field_details.name: segments.year
